  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to see the emails in a chat conversation as mailto links so that I will be able to send email directly by clicking on them.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: The email addresses inside a conversation are not handled properly.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\n\r\nThe emails should be visualized as mailto links and should allow to click on them to send an electronic message to the selected address.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\n\r\nThe emails are handled as regular URLs catching the email domain only. \r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open a chat window\r\n- Enter a valid email address \r\n\r\n### Solution\r\n[comment]: # (Please summarise the solution and provide a task list on what needs to be fixed.)\r\n*Summary*: The emails should be handled as mailto links giving an option to select an external application to be used for sending a message to the selected address. \r\n\r\n- [ ] Handle the emails as mailto links\r\n- [ ] Give the end-users a choice to select an external email application for sending an email\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: \r\n\r\n- [ ] Android: 0.9.20, Nightly build \"June 18\", http://artifacts.status.im:8081/artifactory/nightlies-local/im.status.ethereum-b40b04-n-fl.apk\r\n\r\n- [ ] iOS: 0.9.19 (6031)\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Android or iOS.)\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n\r\n![email](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5781465/41594584-7efe7c40-73cc-11e8-991f-3bbde5e0fbc3.png)\r\n\r\n\n\n<blockquote></blockquote>",
